obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4458)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945&sectionId=4458&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Asian Development`
  line `Bank Act, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 19th, December, 1966, vide notification No. S.O. 3803(E), dated 8th, December, 1966, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4459)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945&sectionId=4459&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Agreement" means the Agreement for the establishment and operation of the international`
  line `body known as the Asian Development Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) "Bank" means the Asian Development Bank established under the Agreement.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4460)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Payments to Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945&sectionId=4460&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be paid out of the Consolidated Fund of India, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, all such sums as may, from time to time, be`
  line `required for the purpose of paying,--`
  line
  line `(a) the subscriptions payable by the Central Government to the Bank under paragraphs 1, 2 and 3`
  line `of Article 5 of the Agreement;`
  line
  line `(b) any commission, fees or other charges payable by the Central Government to the Bank under`
  line `Article 16 of the Agreement;`
  line
  line `(c) any sums payable by the Central Government to the Bank under paragraph 1 of Article 25 of`
  line `the Agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, if it thinks fit so to do, create and issue to the Bank, in such form as`
  line `it thinks fit, any such non-interest bearing and non-negotiable notes or other obligations as are provided`
  line `for by paragraph 3 of Article 6 of the Agreement.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4461)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Reserve Bank to be depository for Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945&sectionId=4461&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Reserve Bank of India shall be the depository of`
  line `the Indian currency holdings of the Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4462)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Conferment of status and certain immunities, exemptions and privileges on Bank and conferment of certain immunities, exemptions and privileges on its officers and employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945&sectionId=4462&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law, the provisions of`
  line `the Agreement set out in the Schedule shall have the force of law in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in Article 56 of the Agreement shall be construed as--`
  line
  line `(a) entitling the Bank to import into India goods free of any duty of customs without any`
  line `restriction on their subsequent sale therein; or`
  line
  line `(b) conferring on the Bank any exemption from duties or taxes which from part of the price of`
  line `goods sold; or`
  line
  line `(c) conferring on the Bank any exemption from duties or taxes which are in fact no more than`
  line `charges for services rendered.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Schedule in`
  line `conformity with any amendments, duly made and adopted, of the provisions of the Agreement set out`
  line therein.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4463)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945&sectionId=4463&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4464)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Notifications issued under section 5 and rules made under section 6 to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945&sectionId=4464&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00015_196618_1517807319945
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every notification issued under sub- section (2) of section 5 and every rule made under`
  line `section 6 shall be laid as soon as may be after it is issued or made before each House of Parliament while`
  line `it is in session for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one session or ^2`
  line `[in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification in the notification or, as the`
  line `case may be, in the rule, or both Houses agree that the notification or rule should not be issued or made,`
  line `the notification or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the`
  line `case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that notification or rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive session aforesaid" (w.e.f. 15-3-1983).`
